# Task

Create CallResult<O> that wraps successful prediction output with rich metadata.

## File to Create
`crates/dspy-rs/src/core/call_result.rs`

## Type Definition

```rust
use indexmap::IndexMap;
use rig::message::ToolCall;
use crate::{Flag, LmUsage};

/// Result of a successful Predict<S>::call_with_meta()
/// 
/// Contains the typed output plus per-field metadata for debugging
/// and introspection.
pub struct CallResult<O> {
    /// The typed output struct
    pub output: O,

    /// Raw LLM response text
    pub raw_response: String,

    /// Token usage statistics
    pub lm_usage: LmUsage,

    /// Tool calls made during generation (if any)
    pub tool_calls: Vec<ToolCall>,

    /// Results of tool executions (if any)
    pub tool_executions: Vec<String>,

    /// Node ID in trace DAG (if tracing enabled)
    pub node_id: Option<usize>,

    /// Per-field parsing metadata, keyed by Rust field name
    fields: IndexMap<String, FieldMeta>,
}

/// Metadata about how a single field was parsed
#[derive(Debug, Clone)]
pub struct FieldMeta {
    /// Raw text extracted between markers
    pub raw_text: String,

    /// Parsing flags from jsonish (what coercions applied)
    pub flags: Vec<Flag>,

    /// Results of check/assert constraints
    pub checks: Vec<ConstraintResult>,
}

/// Result of evaluating a constraint
#[derive(Debug, Clone)]
pub struct ConstraintResult {
    /// Constraint label (from #[check(label="...")])
    pub label: String,

    /// The constraint expression
    pub expression: String,

    /// Whether constraint passed
    pub passed: bool,
}

impl<O> CallResult<O> {
    /// Get parsing flags for a field (e.g., "was this coerced from string?")
    pub fn field_flags(&self, field: &str) -> &[Flag] {
        self.fields.get(field)
            .map(|m| m.flags.as_slice())
            .unwrap_or(&[])
    }

    /// Get constraint results for a field
    pub fn field_checks(&self, field: &str) -> &[ConstraintResult] {
        self.fields.get(field)
            .map(|m| m.checks.as_slice())
            .unwrap_or(&[])
    }

    /// Get raw text that was parsed for a field
    pub fn field_raw(&self, field: &str) -> Option<&str> {
        self.fields.get(field).map(|m| m.raw_text.as_str())
    }

    /// Get all field names that have metadata
    pub fn field_names(&self) -> impl Iterator<Item = &str> {
        self.fields.keys().map(|s| s.as_str())
    }

    /// Check if any constraints failed (but weren't asserts)
    pub fn has_failed_checks(&self) -> bool {
        self.fields.values()
            .flat_map(|m| &m.checks)
            .any(|c| \!c.passed)
    }
}
```

## Usage Example

```rust
let result = predict.call_with_meta(input).await?;

// Access typed output
println\!("Answer: {}", result.output.answer);

// Debug: what was the raw text for 'confidence'?
if let Some(raw) = result.field_raw("confidence") {
    println\!("Raw confidence text: {}", raw);
}

// Check: did any soft constraints fail?
for check in result.field_checks("confidence") {
    if \!check.passed {
        eprintln\!("Warning: check '{}' failed", check.label);
    }
}

// Debug: was coercion applied?
for flag in result.field_flags("count") {
    println\!("Parsing flag: {:?}", flag);
}
```

## Why IndexMap?

Preserves insertion order (output field order), which is useful for debugging and consistent iteration.

